        "timestamp": "2019-09-12 13:50:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> > > > Patch Set 2:\n>  > > >\n>  > > > remerge\n>  > >\n>  > > This will not succeed a 2nd time - already succeeded once.\n>  > \n>  > Never saw a \"Build Successful\" message after the merge.\n> \n> Looks like the build ran.  Maybe it just never added the \"success\" message to the review.  Anyway, appears it just started a build again anyway.\n\nYeah it doesn't post a message here - don't know why. But the command I posted 9/10 worked. But Liam's yesterday didn't so we have a failed job being listed. Not a big deal because its done, but may be confusing for folks as these release jobs can only succeed once.",
