        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-12 13:58:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Yeah it doesn't post a message here - don't know why. But the\n > command I posted 9/10 worked. But Liam's yesterday didn't so we\n > have a failed job being listed. Not a big deal because its done,\n > but may be confusing for folks as these release jobs can only\n > succeed once.\n\nWe're probably talking about two different things.  Yeah, I've never seen it post a \"success\" message after a \"stage-release\".  However, it normally posts a \"success\" message after a \"successfully merged\" message, but it didn't do that here - I do know there was some glitch in the jenkins-gerrit communication during the build backlog the other day; maybe that's why it didn't show up.",
